com.oracle.truffle.api.object

Interface DynamicObjectFactory


  • public interface DynamicObjectFactory
    This factory can be used to create a new DynamicObject from an initial shape, with its instance properties initialized to the values passed to DynamicObjectFactory.newInstance(Object...).
    Since:
    0.8 or earlier
    See Also:
    Shape.createFactory()

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Shape getShape() 
      DynamicObject newInstance(Object... initialValues)
      Create a new DynamicObject and initialize instance properties with the provided values.

    • Method Detail

      • newInstance

        DynamicObject newInstance(Object... initialValues)
        Create a new DynamicObject and initialize instance properties with the provided values. Exactly as many values are required as there are instance properties.
        Parameters:
        initialValues - the values to initialize the object with, in order.
        Returns:
        a new DynamicObject initialized with the provided values.
        Since:
        0.8 or earlier

      • getShape

        Shape getShape()
        Returns:
        the shape of objects created by this factory.
        Since:
        0.8 or earlier
